Rating: 3
In honor of a holiday characterized by palm trees rather than snowflakes, my surrogate family and I christened Christmas dinner 'tropical,' and set about collecting recipes -- of which this cake was to be the coup de grace. Too late I discovered that the minor matter of adding coconut milk to the batter was missing from the instructions. Our milk was unsweetened, our rum cheap, and our thimble of vanilla insufficient. After two hours of preparation, expectations were high, blood sugar low, and festivity on the wane. Under hammer and chisel, the coconut flew off our three-story deck. The cake appeared to have collapsed on itself, and the icing was runny. Yet it turned out irresistibly delicious, and here's how: - start with a hot rum toddy - broil that accursed coconut - add a tbsp vanilla to batter - make a third more icing & add confectioner's sugar - MORE RUM - but not Captain Morgan from the gas station. Voila!

