Rating: 2
The overnite soaking is the trick--do not skimp on the soak! I never did find the coco lopez or any sweetened coconut cream, for that matter, so I just got some coconut milk and added confectioner's sugar to taste. I thought the amount of rum the recipe called for was woefully inadequate so I liberally increased th rum I added to the cake batter and the icing. The coconut toasting and shaving was a bit of an ordeal, but now that I know how to do it it'll go easier next time. That being said, I'm not sure I'd make this again. I found it rather bland and the texture was not the creamy one I'd imagined it would've had. It was definitely soaked so I don't know what I could've done differently. Luckily, I did add rum caramelized bananas as a topping and IMO, this added the needed pizazz. Everyone, including the b-day boy, seemed to love this cake...I'm the only one who didn't go crazy over it. Not bad and it really does look nice, but not the yummiest cake I've ever had.

