This was excellent! I made it for a dessert party on my birthday for which I made eight different cakes (most from this site) and this one was many people's--and my own--favorite. To the question about soaking overnight: I made the cake portion the night before I served and thought it was important to soak in the cream of coconut while the cake was still warm. I will not change anything the next time I make this--and it's so easy! I thought the rum flavor was pronounced so be sure to use good-quality rum in the icing. Whole Foods sells shavings of coconut which was helpful so that I didn't have to wrestle with a whole coconut and a machete right before my cocktail party for 30 people:)

